    <h2>Who We Are</h2>
    <p>The Retiree Report is an educational website operated by a licensed Medicare insurance agent serving North
      Carolina and South Carolina. This site provides plain-language Medicare information and connects visitors with
      a licensed agent — no middlemen, no call centers.</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect information only when you voluntarily provide it — for example, when you subscribe to our
      newsletter or reach out by phone or email.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email address</strong> — collected when you subscribe to the newsletter</li>
      <li><strong>Name</strong> — if you provide it when subscribing or contacting us</li>
      <li><strong>Phone number</strong> — only if you call or text us directly</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not use contact forms that collect personal information without your explicit action. We do not collect
      sensitive health or financial data through this website.</p>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>Information you provide is used only for the purposes you'd expect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Sending the newsletter you signed up for</li>
      <li>Responding to questions or consultation requests you initiate</li>
      <li>Providing Medicare guidance you've asked for</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your information to anyone.</p>

    <h2>Newsletter</h2>
    <p>If you subscribe to The Retiree Report newsletter, your email address is stored through our email service
      provider. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link included in every email. We will honor unsubscribe
      requests promptly.</p>

    <h2>Cookies and Analytics</h2>
    <p>This site may use basic analytics tools (such as Google Analytics) to understand how visitors use the site —
      things like which pages are most visited and what devices people use. This data is aggregated and anonymous;
      it is not tied to your identity. No tracking cookies are used for advertising purposes.</p>
    <p>You can disable cookies in your browser settings at any time.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
    <p>Some pages may link to external websites (such as Medicare.gov). We are not responsible for the privacy
      practices of those sites. We recommend reviewing the privacy policy of any site you visit.</p>

    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>This site is intended for adults approaching or in retirement. We do not knowingly collect information from
      anyone under the age of 18.</p>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable precautions to protect your information. However, no method of transmission over the
      internet is completely secure. We encourage you to use caution when sharing personal information online.</p>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>You may request to view, correct, or delete any personal information we hold about you by contacting us
      directly. We will respond to reasonable requests promptly.</p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we'll update the "last updated" date at the top of
      this page. We encourage you to review this page periodically.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about this privacy policy? Reach out directly — contact information is on the <a
        href="/pages/work-with-me.html">Work With Me</a> page.</p>

  </div>
